g.";i:11;s:176:"A force-sensitive switch that detects if the motor torque is excessive typically tripped by incorrect adjustment or by leaving a solid object in the way of the descending door.";i:12;s:156:"How to fix the garage door when it opens by itselfSuddenly my garage door was opening on its own at least couple times a day it starter when i tried to set.";i:13;s:55:"What To Do If Your Garage Door Keeps Closing Reopening.";i:14;s:177:"The garage door is likely the most used entryway to your home and its essential to keep this fixture regularly maintained to ensure lasting safety convenience and peace of mind.";i:15;s:161:"One regular garage door issue many homeowners face is clicking the control panel to close your door only to have it immediately reopen once it reaches the floor.";i:16;s:38:"My garage door keeps bouncing back up.";i:17;s:23:"Heres what will fix it.";i:18;s:60:"If playback doesnt begin shortly try restarting your device.";i:19;s:47:"Videos you watch may be added to the TVs watch.";i:20;s:106:"If the wires appear to be in good shape next look at the control button mounted near your side entry door.";i:21;s:43:"If it is old or dirty the button may stick.";i:22;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:23;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:24;s:72:"There are a few unusual factors that can cause your door open by itself.";i:25;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:26;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:27;s:39:"I have three Genie garage door openers.";i:28;s:72:"Two years after installation one started opening and closing on its own.";i:29;s:122:"I took the batteries out of the transmitters shut off the switch on the door button and reprogrammed the openclose limits.";i:30;s:39:"Garage door opener motor keeps running.";i:31;s:101:"I have an older opener and wanted to adjust the height so I could get a few more inches of clearance.";i:32;s:45:"There were 2 adjustment knobs open and close.";i:33;s:91:"When the door was in the open position I turned the open knob and it moved up a few inches.";i:34;s:52:"Then closed the door and it didnt close all the way.";i:35;s:33:"Garage door closes after opening.";i:36;s:118:"Recently my garage door started closing immediately after being opened via the remote or the button inside the garage.";i:37;s:86:"After several attempts to open it it finally stops going down again or if you push it.";i:38;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:39;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:40;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:41;s:44:"Doing this can save you some amount of cash.";i:42;s:41:"Additionally a simple rebooting can help.";i:43;s:45:"Garage Door Reverses when opening or closing.";i:44;s:174:"If your garage door reverses anytime you open or close it there could be a problem with your safety sensor incorrect force settings or there is an obstruction on the doorway.";i:45;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:46;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:47;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:48;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:49;s:34:"It may be your garage door sensor.";i:50;s:101:"There are four common problems with garage door sensors three of these homeowners can fix themselves.";i:51;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:52;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:53;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:54;s:145:"When the garage door is closing and it doesnt reach the fully closed position it assumes there is an obstruction in the way and then it reverses.";i:55;s:82:"This helps protect objects which may not have been detected by the safety sensors.";i:56;s:113:"Here are the troubleshooting steps to follow when your Craftsman garage door opener reverses after fully closing.";i:57;s:29:"Try to close the garage door.";i:58;s:130:"If it still automatically begins to reverse or open back up turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn and test it again.";i:59;s:32:"Continue turning the down screw.";i:60;s:128:"The photo eyes send an infrared beam across the bottom of your garage door opening if that beam is broken the door will reverse.";i:61;s:135:"This is a safety feature that has been added to garage door openers to help prevent the door from closing on a car pet or even a child.";}}